Use the standard library
This is how to split_words of txt:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that current is []
   Remember that n is txt's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that c is item i in txt
      Remember that sep is 0
      When c is 32, then:
         Remember that sep is 1
      End when
      When c is 44, then:
         Remember that sep is 1
      End when
      When c is " ", then:
         Remember that sep is 1
      End when
      When c is ",", then:
         Remember that sep is 1
      End when
      When sep is 1, then:
         When current's length is more than 0, then:
            Add result to current
            Remember that current is []
         End when
      But, if not:
         Add current to c
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   When current's length is more than 0, then:
      Add result to current
   End when
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> split_words of [72, 101, 108, 108, 111, 32, 119, 111, 114, 108, 100, 33]
[[72, 101, 108, 108, 111], [119, 111, 114, 108, 100, 33]]
>>> split_words of "Hello world!"
["Hello", "world!"]
>>> split_words of "Hello,world!"
["Hello", "world!"]